

fidoip installation for CRUX Linux

1. Install fidoip port:

cd /usr/ports/falcony/fidoip ; pkgmk -d -i ; pkgmk -c

2. Download fidoip-last_version.tar from http://sourceforge.net/projects/fidoip/

3. Read documentation on http://fidoip.wiki.sourceforge.net/

4. tar -xzpf fidoip-last_version.tar

cd fidoip-last_version

su

run script relinkapps.sh to reling application and libraries:

./relinkapps.sh 

Setup configuration for youself:
 
./setup_config.bash

Setup permission for your_self:

./set_perm.sh your_login

Using your login name run recv script to recieve fido messages, ge, gl or g script to start GoldED+ editor.
Send them messaged by send script.

For more detail check http://fidoip.wiki.sourceforge.net/

        
